Context and Main Purpose:

Farming will be very challenging in near future due to climate changes, =
industrialization and population increase. According to the UN Food and =
Agriculture Organization, the world will need to produce 70% more food =
in 2050 than it did in 2006 in order to feed the growing population of =
the Earth. Smart farming or precision agriculture is emerging to meet =
this       demands by providing the farmers with decision-making support =
to increase production capabilities and reduce costs.=20

Smart farming requires the collection of data from various sources =
including sensors, global positioning systems, communication systems, =
social networks apis, weather data =E2=80=A6 and requires also big data =
storage and analysis. A major challenge in precision agriculture today =
is how to analyze these data efficiently and use them to improve farming =
decisions.

The LISITE laboratory of ISEP is working with an industrial partner =
(Cap2020) on an innovative project for smart farming =E2=80=9CIDEAC=E2=80=9D=
. The IDEAC project aims to help farmers to make precise and predictive =
decisions for maximum productivity, greater profits and more =
sustainability.=20

An open source architecture have been proposed to address the different =
challenges (heterogeneous data collection (sensors, server apis, social =
networks=E2=80=A6.), big data storage and data analytics=E2=80=A6).  In =
this context, we are looking for a postdoc with strong background in   =
Machine Learning and Data Analysis.=20

The goal of this postdoc is to propose deep learning prediction models =
for each data source (or use case) and to transform them into aggregate =
ones. The proposed models will be implemented using TensorFlow and =
integrated in the global architecture.

Requirements:=20

=C2=B7       The candidate should have experience in machine learning, =
neuronal networks or data sciences

=C2=B7      Experience in Big Data technologies (Big Data processing and =
management) and  distributed systems: Hadoop, Spark, HBase is a plus

=C2=B7      Knowledge of Machine Learning Tools and Frameworks (e.g =
TensorFlow)

=C2=B7      Good scripting and coding skills (python, java or C++)

=C2=B7      Autonomous and team working

Duration: 9 months

Start Date: ASAP

Hosting team: LISITE, Institut Sup=C3=A9rieur d=E2=80=99=C3=89lectronique =
de Paris (ISEP)  (https://www.isep.fr/ <https://www.isep.fr/>)

10 Rue de Vanves Issy Les Moulineaux

Application instructions:To apply, please send a mail and CV to =
raja.chiky@isep.fr <mailto:raja.chiky@isep.fr>

Raja Chiky
raja.chiky@isep.fr




